analyzed_images.image_description: The image is a map of the VATSIM Germany Sektor Bottrop (EDDL_BOT_APP) used for flight simulation purposes. The map outlines various airspace sectors with their respective altitude limits and frequencies. The sectors are labeled BOT1, BOT2, BOT3, BOT4, BOT5, BOT6, BOT7, DUS52, NOR2, DKA3, and others. Each sector has specific altitude ranges and ground frequencies indicated. The map also includes adjacent airspace sectors such as EHAA CTA E2, EHMC TMA E, HMM2, HMM1, PADH1, and others, with their respective altitude limits and frequencies. The map is intended for flight simulation use only and is not to be used for real-world flight.

The image is a map of an airspace sector, specifically FIR Langen, dated 07.01.2022, and created by VACC Germany. The map outlines various airspace sectors with their respective altitude limits and ground (GND) levels. 

Key features include:
- Different sectors labeled with codes such as DU51, DU52, DU53, etc.
- Each sector has specified altitude limits, for example, DU51 ranges from ground level (GND) to 75, DU52 ranges from 155 to 245, and so on.
- The sectors are outlined with boundaries and some are shaded in orange, indicating a specific grouping or area of interest.
- The map includes other sectors like HMM1, BOT1, NOR1, PADH1, and others, each with their own altitude limits.
- There are arrows and lines indicating connections or transitions between sectors.

Overall, the map provides a detailed view of the airspace structure within FIR Langen, useful for air traffic control and navigation purposes.

metadata.abstract: The document 'EBG 1 [BOT, DUS]' provides detailed information for flight simulator use, specifically for the Bottrop (EDDL BOT APP) and Düsseldorf Terminal (EDDL_APP) sectors. It includes sector boundaries, frequencies, and main sector tasks. The Bottrop sector handles arrivals via TEBRO to PISAP from EHAA and departures via MODRU, NETEX, MEVEL, and SONEB, as well as traffic for EDLV and ETNG. The Düsseldorf sector manages in- and outbounds for EDDL and EDLN. Both sectors have detailed Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) available for EDDL arrivals. The document emphasizes that it is for simulator use only and not for real-world flight, and it is provided by VATSIM Germany.
